The paper focuses on face detection using the Faster R-CNN model, which is a popular object detection algorithm in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper involves training the model on a large dataset, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of deep learning techniques also suggests cs.MM (Multimedia) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its results on two benchmarks, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
